          "anchor": "Discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The agent updates its own position, rotation, and velocity according to its goals when you call its ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.gameplaykit/documentation/GameplayKit/GKAgent2D/update(deltaTime:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "However, you can still directly change the rotation of an agent. Do this when you want to move a static agent (that is, one with no goals) or override an agent’s behavior as a direct result of user input.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
